If you are visiting any fort in India, I would suggest you to know its history before going there because after knowing history we get more curious and interested to see that place….
📍Amer fort
Baradari at Man Singh Palace…… 

One of the place to see if you are in Amer fort. This place has its own history as This is the oldest structure in the entire fort as it stands today. There is a pavilion in the middle of the courtyard surrounded by living quarters.
There is a saying that the king had 12 wives, each from different zodiac signs. And so there are 12 rooms on all sides of the courtyard.
Each places has its own significance and beauty in itself.

latestPosts.caption:
Planning a trip to Vrindavan? Here’s everything you need to know for a peaceful and divine Banke Bihari ji darshan 💛

I visited on a weekday at 7:30 AM, and trust me — it was the most calming experience. No crowd, no chaos — just pure spiritual bliss 🙏

From what to wear, best darshan timings, nearby food spots, to travel tips — I’ve shared it all in this post. Make sure to save & share with anyone visiting soon!

🚶‍♀️ Pro Tip: Flat sandals only! You’ll need to walk from parking to the temple gate — heels will regret coming 😅

Comment “Radhey Radhey” if you’ve experienced this magic!
And yes, don’t forget to treat yourself at Royal Bharti Shop — their kachori-jalebi combo is iconic that too with lassi … 

📩 DM if you want help planning your visit!
